#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.120, sc8
msgctxt "an3.21:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantañca samiddhaṃ āyasmantañca mahākoṭṭhikaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta said to Saviṭṭha and Mahākoṭṭhita, "

msgctxt "an3.21:8.2"
msgid "“byākataṃ kho, āvuso, amhehi sabbeheva yathāsakaṃ paṭibhānaṃ. "
msgstr "“Each of us has spoken from the heart. "

msgctxt "an3.21:8.3"
msgid "Āyāmāvuso, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocessāma. "
msgstr "Come, reverends, let’s go to the Buddha, and tell him about this. "

msgctxt "an3.21:8.4"
msgid "Yathā no bhagavā byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti. "
msgstr "As he answers, so we’ll remember it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.21:8.5"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā ca samiddho āyasmā ca mahākoṭṭhiko āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied. "

msgctxt "an3.21:8.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ca sāriputto āyasmā ca samiddho āyasmā ca mahākoṭṭhiko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta, Saviṭṭha, and Mahākoṭṭhita went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. "

msgctxt "an3.21:8.7"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto yāvatako ahosi āyasmatā ca samiddhena āyasmatā ca mahākoṭṭhikena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi. "
msgstr "Then Sāriputta told the Buddha of all they had discussed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.21:9.1"
msgid "“Na khvettha, sāriputta, sukaraṃ ekaṃsena byākātuṃ: "
msgstr "“In this matter, Sāriputta, it’s not easy to definitively declare that "

msgctxt "an3.21:9.2"
msgid "‘ayaṃ imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ puggalānaṃ abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro cā’ti. "
msgstr "one of these three people is finest. "

#. VAR: svāssa → svāyaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1) | soyaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: svāssa → svāyaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1) | soyaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: sopassa → soyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.21:9.3"
msgid "Ṭhānañhetaṃ, sāriputta, vijjati yvāyaṃ puggalo saddhāvimutto svāssa arahattāya paṭipanno, yvāyaṃ puggalo kāyasakkhī svāssa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā, yo cāyaṃ puggalo diṭṭhippatto sopassa sakadāgāmī vā anāgāmī vā. "
msgstr "In some cases, a person who is freed by faith is practicing for perfection, while the personal witness and the one attained to view are once-returners or non-returners. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an3.21:10.1"
